<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ruehe, ROK Counterpart Discuss Military Exchanges </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ruehe, ROK Counterpart Discuss Military Exchanges </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0405131094 Seoul YONHAP in English 1303 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0405131094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn, May 4 (YONHAP) -- Visiting South Korean 
Defense Minister Yi Pyong-tae conferred with his German 
counterpart, Minister Volker Ruehe, here Wednesday [4 May] and 
they agreed on stepped-up military exchanges and cooperation 
between their countries. 
  The two ministers in particular shared the view that the 
North Korean nuclear question is the factor of major threat to 
stability in Northeast Asia let alone the Korean peninsula and 
that Pyongyang's nuclear development should be thwarted by all 
means. 
  During the meeting held at the German Defense Ministry, the 
two ministers adopted a joint statement on the promotion of 
defense and military exchanges and cooperation. 
  The statement called for the diversification of bilateral 
policy and strategic dialogues and expansion of mutual 
cooperation in easing tension in disputed areas. 
  Defense sources said the statement was significant in that 
it 
is the first document Germany adopted with a non-NATO member 
country for expanded cooperation in the defense area. 
  The statement specifically featured mutual consultations on 
basic defense and military policies, exchanges of information 
and personnel, and stepped-up cooperation in defense industry, 
education and training. 
  Minister Yi is expected to visit the German Eastern Corps 
Headquarters and Berlin on Thursday before leaving for Seoul. 

</TEXT>

