<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Praises EU Expansion </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Praises EU Expansion </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405164894 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1626 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405164894 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel has 
expressed pleasure at the "overwhelming approval" by the 
European Parliament of the entry of Austria, Sweden, Finland, 
and Norway into the European Union [EU]. A further great and 
important step toward the enlargement of the EU has been taken, 
Kinkel said in Bonn on Wednesday [3 May]. Kinkel said he is 
confident that the last hurdles will also now be overcome and 
that the referenda and ratification processes in the individual 
states will be brought to a brisk and positive conclusion. 
Kinkel stressed that the Federal Government will do everything 
to ensure the treaties of accession were ratified in good time 
in Germany, so that the four European Free Trade Association 
states will become equal members of the EU on 1 January next 
year. 

</TEXT>

