<H3> <TI>   Berlusconi Responds </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berlusconi Responds </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405132994 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1249 GMT 
4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0405132994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister-Designate Silvio Berlusconi has given 
only an oblique reply to Umberto Bossi's request to suspend the 
summit meetings between the heads of the Freedom Alliance: "He 
thinks that he needs a pause for thought; however, I will 
continue on the path that I have chosen. I received the mandate 
from President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro and from the voters, and I 
must carry out my duty. I will keep the allies informed," he 
stressed, "But I will act in accordance with Article 92 of the 
Constitution." 
  Bossi did not attend the scheduled meeting with Berlusconi 
and Gianfranco Fini. Fini said that the League "is wrong to 
make conditions." The obstacle is still the same one: the 
Interior Ministry. 

</TEXT>

