<H3> <TI>   Government Welcomes Outcome of EU Membership Voting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Welcomes Outcome of EU Membership Voting </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405172094 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1600 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0405172094 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The government of Finland has welcomed the outcome 
of the vote of the European Parliament on Finland's EU [European 
Union] membership. Prime Minister Esko Aho described the 
outcome of the vote as a positive piece of news, and Foreign 
Trade Minister Pertti Salolainen as a dramatically good result. 
The government was delighted that a larger majority than 
expected of European deputies voted for Finland's membership. 
The government was following the voting by the European 
Parliament at its evening meeting at the Prime Minister's 
residence in Kesaeranta. The government agreed at its meeting 
that the date for the EU national referendum and the size of 
national subsidies will be decided by the 26 May. 

</TEXT>

