<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   EU Referendum Date To Be Announced by 26 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EU Referendum Date To Be Announced by 26 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0405191494 Paris AFP in English 1851 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0405191494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Helsinki, May 4 (AFP) -- The Finnish Government will 
submit to parliament a date for the referendum on European Union 
(EU) membership by May 26 at the latest, Finnish Prime Minister 
Esko Aho stated Wednesday [4 May]. 
  Aho has previously talked of holding a November referendum, 
while Finnish President Martti Ahtisaari has discussed the 
possibility of a September or October referendum. 
  Sweden will hold its referendum November 13 and Austria on 
June 12. Norway has yet to announce a date. 
  Meanwhile, Finnish Foreign Trade Minister Pertti Salolainen, 
who together with Foreign Minister Heikki Haavisto negotiated 
Finland's membership agreement in Brussels, said he was pleased 
with the European Parliament's decision Wednesday to admit the 
four applicant countries. 
  "This is a fantastic result if one considers that 259 votes 
were required for membership, and we were well over that by 100 
and there were few opponents," he said. 

</TEXT>

