<H3> <TI>   Prime Minister Hails European Parliament's Vote </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prime Minister Hails European Parliament's Vote </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0405192494 Paris AFP in English 1858 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0405192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Oslo, May 4 (AFP) -- The European Parliament's 
decision to approve Norway's European Union (EU) membership 
agreement demonstrates that Norway is welcome in the EU, 
Norwegian Prime Minister Gro Harlem Brundtland said Wednesday [4 
May]. 
  "The decision also shows that the parliamentarians support 
the negotiation results, which ensure special Norwegian needs 
such as Norwegian agriculture, an active regional policy and new 
possibilities for support for fisheries," she said. 
  The European Parliament accepted Norway's agreement 
Wednesday 
with 374 votes out of 456. 
  Meanwhile, Norwegian Trade Minister Grete Knudsen, who was 
responsible for negotiating the EU agreement in Brussels, said 
Wednesday that a date for the Norwegian referendum would be 
decided upon by May 27. 
  Swedes will vote November 13, Austria June 12, while Finland 
has yet to set a date. 

</TEXT>

