<F P=101> Norway </F>
<H3> <TI>   Oslo: No Peacekeeping Troops for Nagorno-Karabakh </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Oslo: No Peacekeeping Troops for Nagorno-Karabakh </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405224794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 2145 
GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0405224794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Igor Pshenichnikov] </F>
  [Excerpt] Oslo, 5 May -- Norway has decided not to send its 
military contingent to Nagorno-Karabakh to take part in the 
peacekeeping operation planned by the Conference on Security and 
Cooperation in Europe [CSCE], Kirsti Skjerven, an official 
spokesperson of the Norwegian Defense Ministry, told ITAR-TASS 
in an interview. 
  She said that the CSCE had appealed to Norway in March to 
take part in a planned peacekeeping operation in 
Nagorno-Karabakh. After studying this matter and taking into 
account the situation in Bosnia, where Norwegian servicemen form 
part of the UN peacekeeping force, Norway's Defense Ministry 
considered it impossible to allocate a military contingent for a 
peacekeeping mission in the area of the Armenian-Azeri conflict. 
Kirsti Skjerven stressed: "The Ministry of Defense of Norway 
believes that it is necessary to concentrate our peacekeeping 
forces in one place and not scatter them about. The funds 
earmarked by the Norwegian parliament for maintaining 
peacekeeping forces abroad can thus be used in the best way." 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

