<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cindoruk Returns From `Positive' Talks in France </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cindoruk Returns From `Positive' Talks in France </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0505083094 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
0430 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0505083094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Husamettin Cindoruk, speaker of the Turkish Grand 
National Assembly, who concluded his official visit to France as 
the guest of his French counterpart, has returned to Turkey. In 
a statement at Istanbul's Ataturk Airport, Cindoruk said that 
during his visit, he held positive and fruitful meetings with 
the French president, parliamentary officials, and 
representatives of political parties. 
  Noting that he held a one and-a-half-hour meeting with 
French 
President Francois Mitterrand, Cindoruk remarked that the 
meeting yielded beneficial and important results for Turkey. 
Cindoruk said that during the meeting, he had the opportunity 
to respond to some of Mitterrand's views and concerns. Cindoruk 
stated: I believe that I was able to explain Turkey's problems 
to him properly. There is no concern with regard to our 
country's democratization and human rights and its close ties to 
West Europe. If there were any reasons for concern on these 
subjects, they were presented to us and we offered the necessary 
explanations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

