<F P=100> BENELUX </F>
<F P=101> Belgium </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Calls For Increased Defense Budget </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Calls For Increased Defense Budget </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0405143594 Groot-Bijgaarden DE STANDAARD in Dutch 4 May 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> BR0405143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Groot-Bijgaarden DE STANDAARD </F>
<F P=105>  Dutch </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Delcroix Wants To Increase Army </F>
Budget"] 
  [Text] Belgian Defense Minister Leo Delcroix believes that 
the military budget needs to be increased. Yesterday, the 
minister was answering questions from reporters during the 
"Joint Effort 1994" maneuver, a staff exercise in which a 
complete division is deployed to impose and enforce peace on 
behalf of the United Nations. 
  Minister Delcroix said "that a political consensus is 
emerging in favor of once again increasing funding for the Army 
in the following legislative session." He urges less rapid 
participation in UN operations, but said that such participation 
should be better prepared and equipped with more resources. 
  Under the leadership of Lieutenant General Francis 
Briquemont, the former UN commander in Bosnia-Herzegovina, the 
Army is holding a staff exercise through today in Leopoldsburg 
[Belgium]. In such exercises, no units are deployed on the 
ground but realistic procedures are followed. The goal of the 
exercise is peace enforcement, restoring peace through the 
potential deployment of all possible means. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

