<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Comments on Denktas UN Letter </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Comments on Denktas UN Letter </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0405142294 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0405142294 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis said it is 
up to the UN Security Council to show determination--as it is 
showing on other international issues--or to let the Turkish 
intervention in Cyprus slander its image and international law. 
The spokesman made his statement to the Cyprus Broadcasting 
Corporation commenting on a letter from Turkish Cypriot leader 
Rauf Denktas to the UN secretary general. In his letter Denktas 
criticizes the UN envoys and says that he is ready to continue 
with the talks if the proposals included in the UN documents are 
changed. 
  The spokesman said: In his letter, Denktas is again trying 
to implement a policy of delaying. The Greek Cypriot side's 
actions and demarches will be made after the UN secretary 
general submits his report and the National Council confers. At 
the National Council, President Glavkos Kliridhis will explain 
his thoughts for discussion and decisionmaking. 

</TEXT>

