<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry, Parties Hail Israel-PLO Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0505103494 Athens ET-1 Television Network in Greek 1800 
GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0505103494 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ET-1 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Referring to the historic Israeli-PLO Agreement, the 
Foreign Ministry, representing the European Union [EU], stressed 
that the EU warmly welcomes the signing of the agreement and 
particularly respects the two sides' decisiveness not to allow 
extremist elements to raise obstacles in front of peace. The EU 
is calling on all sides to play full and positive roles on the 
bilateral and multilateral levels of the peace agreement. 
  New Democracy hailed the agreement between Israel and the 
Palestinians, describing it as a historic and courageous step 
toward a permanent peace settlement in the region. 
  Political Spring expressed hope that the courageous message 
of peace will find imitators in every distressed corner of the 
world, especially Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  A Coalition of the Left and Progress statement notes that 
the 
dream of past decades is now becoming a reality and the lengthy 
struggles of the heroic Palestinian people are justified. 

</TEXT>

