<F P=106> [Statement issued by the Presidential Press Center] </F>
  [Text] The agreement signed between the Israelis and the 
Palestinians in Cairo today on the transfer of Gaza and Jericho 
to Palestinian autonomy constitutes a hopeful turning point in 
the Middle East peace process and has been received with great 
satisfaction. President Suleyman Demirel congratulates the 
Palestinian and Israeli leaders, whose efforts and sacrifices 
have enabled this agreement, and Husni Mubarak, president of the 
friendly and brotherly Arab Republic of Egypt, who has exerted 
efforts towards and made significant contributions to the 
realization of this agreement. Turkey is determined to continue 
its contribution toward the speedy advancement, in the right 
direction, of the Middle East peace process. 

</TEXT>

