<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sri Lankan Anti-LTTE Activist Shot in Paris </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sri Lankan Anti-LTTE Activist Shot in Paris </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK0505114894 Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation 
International Service in English 1045 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK0505114894 </F>
<F P=104>  Colombo Sri Lanka Broadcasting Corporation 
International Service </F>

<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Anti-LTTE [Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam] 
activist, Sabalingam was bumped off in Paris on Sunday [May 1] 
to prevent him from publishing a book on the atrocities 
committed by LTTE and the movement's other inside activities. 
According to reports, he had fled from Colombo to Paris after 
the annihilation of their fellow leader and his organization on 
the orders of Velupillai Prabhakaran. He at first been in the 
LTTE youth movement and was also a close associate of fellow 
leader Sri Sabaratnam. Later, he became an active member of the 
LTTE. For some reason or other, he later (fell out) with him 
and was due to publish a book about LTTE atrocities and their 
other activities. He was reported to have been collecting 
details of LTTE victims and carrying on anti-Tiger campaign in 
France. According to reports reaching Colombo, Sabalingam was 
head of the Mahattaya faction in the Paris office of the LTTE. 
He was shot dead allegedly by Prabhakaran loyalists. 
  The Foreign Ministry has telexed the Sri Lanka Embassy in 
Paris for details of the reported shooting of Sabalingam in 
Paris. Reports said Sabalingam's funeral is being held by Tamil 
organizations in France. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

