<H3> <TI>   Balladur Opens Asian Development Bank Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Balladur Opens Asian Development Bank Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0405135294 Paris LE FIGARO in French 4 May 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> BR0405135294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris LE FIGARO </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Gerard Nirascou: "Balladur in Nice"] </F>
  [Excerpt] Nice -- The prime minister went to Nice yesterday 
to attend the opening ceremony of the 27th General Assembly of 
the Asian Development Bank. Edouard Balladur took advantage of 
the opportunity to forcefully reaffirm France's interest in that 
continent and the desire of our country and Europe to have a 
greater presence there. "The stakes are considerable," the 
prime minister explained, "in the political sphere, the European 
countries and their Asian partners have prime responsibility for 
the security and stability of these continents...and in the 
economic sphere, Europe is the world's leading trading partner 
and is one of the most prosperous markets." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

