<F P=106> [Unattributed article from Brussels EUROPE: "Sir Leon </F>
Brittan Holds Talks in Moscow"] 
  [Text] Sir Leon Brittan returned to Brussels after talks on 
Monday [2 May] in Moscow with Mr. Shokhin. Community circles 
announced that there had been progress in the development of 
plans for an exchange of letters between Russia and the European 
Union to regulate trade in nuclear materials in the framework of 
the partnership and cooperation agreement. However, it was also 
noted that the negotiations are not over and must be pursued. 
The Commission services will undoubtedly contact the 
delegations of the Member States regarding the wording under 
consideration. Pending a compromise on the nuclear dossier (in 
particular the conditions for the import of Russian uranium by 
the EU), two other aspects remain open: the regime of access to 
the Russian market for EU banks and shipping. 

