<F P=106> [Article signed RHR/MPN: "Enlargement: Dehaene Welcomes </F>
European Parliament's Approval"] 
  [Text] Brussels, 4 May (BELGA) -- Prime Minister Jean-Luc 
Dehaene immediately expressed his satisfaction following the 
European Parliament's (EP) approval, on Wednesday [4 May] 
afternoon, of the Accession Treaties to the European Union (EU) 
for Sweden, Finland, Austria, and Norway. 
  "This approval marks a major step along the road to rapid 
and 
effective EU membership for these countries. By the vote of the 
representatives directly elected by European citizens, the EP 
has thus shown that the Union is effectively opening up to such 
an enlargement. In so doing, Europe is giving a very clear 
signal to the citizens of Sweden, Finland, Austria, and Norway, 
confirming that they are welcome within the Union," the Belgian 
leader stated in a communique. 
  "The Belgian Government, which had made EU enlargement one 
of 
the priorities of its presidency, would like to thank the EP for 
having voted on enlargement at this opportune moment." 

</TEXT>

