  [Text] Berlin (DPA) -- South Korean Defense Minister 
Pyong-tae Yi ended his three-day visit to Germany in Berlin on 5 
May. The visitor laid a wreath at the memorial to the 
resistance fighters of 20 July 1944. 
  A Bundeswehr press officer said that on the sidelines of the 
ceremony, the politician had said he did not currently see a 
danger of war for his country. However, the North Korean troops 
were holding military exercises. Tensions between the two parts 
of Korea increased over the past months because of the DPRK's 
nuclear program. 
  The minister had met with his German counterpart, Volker 
Ruehe, in Bonn on 4 May. During their talk, both agreed on 
closer defense and military policy cooperation between the 
Federal Republic of Germany and South Korea. 

