<F P=102>   BR0405142894 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1055 GMT 4 
May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0405142894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Russia/Italy: Italian Firm To Aid </F>
Russian Packaging Industry"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Moscow, May 4 -- The Italian firm Fata has 
signed a deal worth 80 million dollars (130 billion lire) to 
supply equipment and machinery for production of packaging 
materials to a plant in the Russian region of Tyumen, in west 
Siberia, company officials today announced. 
  The plant, to be built on the site of a former petrolium 
industry equipment supplier, is expected to have a yearly 
production of 16,000 [metric] tons of packaging materials 
consisting mainly of aluminum, card and paper sheets. 
  Russia's lack of packaging materials is considered one of 
the 
main reasons for the huge losses incurred by its agricultural 
sector, a situation only partially eased by the country's 
purchase in 1992-1993 of materials worth 190 million dollars. 

</TEXT>

