<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Passes EU Accession Law </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parliament Passes EU Accession Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0505204094 Vienna ORF Television Network in German 2015 
GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0505204094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna ORF Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In a marathon session, parliament gave the go-ahead 
for the referendum on Austria's accession to the European Union 
[EU] on 12 June. The vote was 140 in favor, 35 against the EU 
accession act. In the vote by name, all deputies of the Social 
Democratic Party, the Austrian People's Party, and of the 
Liberal Forum, as well as the Environment spokeswoman of the 
Green Party, Monika Langthaler, voted in favor of EU membership. 

</TEXT>

