<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijani President Arrives on Day-Long Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Azerbaijani President Arrives on Day-Long Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0505131394 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1200 
GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0505131394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Azerbaijani President Geydar Aliyev has arrived on 
a visit in Ankara. Aliyev and the delegation accompanying him 
were received by Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin and other 
officials. 
  Replying to reporters' questions, Aliyev said that the 
Partnership for Peace plan signed by NATO member countries in 
Brussels will be very beneficial for the countries that have 
joined the partnership. He added that the partnership 
principles will make significant contributions to the solution 
of the Azerbaijani-Armenian conflict. 
  Aliyev was later received by President Suleyman Demirel at 
the Cankaya Mansion. Aliyev will return to Azerbaijan today. 

</TEXT>

