<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cetin Comments on Lifting of German Arms Ban </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cetin Comments on Lifting of German Arms Ban </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0505122094 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 0930 GMT 5 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0505122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, May 5 (A.A.) -- Foreign Minister Hikmet 
Cetin returned home on Wednesday [4 May] after taking part in 
the signature ceremony in Cairo giving self-rule to Palestinians 
in the Gaza Strip and Jericho. 
  After his return, Cetin evaluated the removal of the German 
arms ban on Turkey as a normal consequence of Turkish-German 
relations. 
  Germany which suspended arms shipments to Turkey in April, 
on 
claims that these weapons were used in the southeast against 
separatist terrorists, declared the same day that the ban was 
lifted, since the allegations proved to be false. 
  `The decision is proof that efforts to damage German-Turkish 
friendship and cooperation have failed,' Cetin said. 
  `The traditional mutual-trust relations between Turkey and 
Germany have been strengthened once more, after this 
experience,' he said. 

</TEXT>

