<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Leaves for France, Luxembourg </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Leaves for France, Luxembourg </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0505122494 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0505122494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] National Defense Minister Mehmet Golhan has left on 
an official visit to France. In a statement at Esenboga Airport 
prior to his departure, Golhan said that after the three-day 
visit to France as the official guest of French Defense Minister 
Francois Leotard, he will attend the Western European Union 
ministerial meeting to be held in Luxembourg on 9 May. He added 
that he will be discussing issues concerning NATO, Cyprus, 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, Azerbaijan, and international problems with 
French officials. He noted that defense industry cooperation 
activities between the two countries, which have significantly 
developed in recent years, will also be reviewed. 

</TEXT>

