<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   World Bank Approves Privatization Loan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    World Bank Approves Privatization Loan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0505121694 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0505121694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The World Bank will extend a loan of $100 million 
to Turkey within the framework of the privatization program. 
According to a statement issued by the Treasury and Foreign 
Trade Undersecretariat, the World Bank Board of Directors 
discussed and approved a loan for the privatization project and 
the social security network technical assistance. The project 
aims at establishing the necessary infrastructure for the 
success of the privatization program in Turkey, retraining the 
work force in coordination with the privatization process, and 
basing the Public Economic Enterprises on a solid foundation 
within the economy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

