<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mystery Surrounds European Motion on Fascism </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mystery Surrounds European Motion on Fascism </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505165394 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1515 
GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0505165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We will open our news bulletin with a sensational 
piece of news: The European Parliament's condemnation of the 
appointment of any Fascist ministers in the Italian Government 
could in fact be false. The affair of the motion approved by 
the Strasbourg parliament, which has unleashed bitter argument 
in Italy, is shrouded in mystery. 
  The National Alliance alleges that the Italian translation 
of 
the motion has inserted the additional sentence -- following the 
horrors of Fascism and Nazism. This phrase does not appear in 
the French language version of the motion that was approved by 
the European Parliament, nor does it appear in the motion 
translated into the other official parliamentary languages. 
  The incriminating passage completes the appeal to the 
Italian 
Government to respect the values of the European Community. 
According to National Alliance spokesman Francesco Storacce, the 
insertion of the sentence is not a technical oversight, but a 
miserable propaganda exercise. European Parliament President 
Egon Klepsch intends to set up an inquiry. We are awaiting 
further developments. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

