<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bossi: Berlusconi Want `Everything' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bossi: Berlusconi Want `Everything' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0505134494 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1215 GMT 
5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0505134494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Bossi: We Want a Political Ministry"] </F>
  [Text] "For us it is a matter of division of power. We do 
not want Berlusconi to have everything. Our ideals are not up 
for sale and this is why we want a political ministry and not 
only an economic one. We shall be the guarantee; if the 
government were to threaten democracy, it would not last two 
seconds." 
  Bossi seems to agree with [Roberto] Maroni, who offered a 
way 
out to Berlusconi by asking for the Foreign and Treasury 
ministries instead of the Interior Ministry, which is a problem. 
The League leader also attacked the prime minister-designate: 
"He thinks the state is a company he can raid." 

</TEXT>

