<H3> <TI>   Government Comments on Papoulias-Serreqi Meeting </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Comments on Papoulias-Serreqi Meeting </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Denies Tsamidhes Issue Discussed </H4>

<F P=102> NC0505192594 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1700 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0505192594 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos 
commented on an Albanian television report that said that the 
issue of Tsamidhes [Muslims living in Greece who went to Albania 
after World War II] was discussed at the recent meeting between 
Foreign Minister Karolos Papoulias and Albanian Foreign Minister 
Alfred Serreqi in Zurich. Venizelos said the statements are 
inaccurate. Venizelos added that even if the Albanian side had 
raised such an issue, Greece would not have agreed to discuss 
it. [passage omitted] 

