Tirana claims he did--in connection with Albanian claims that 
radio stations and other organizations are being obstructed from 
operating in northern Greece. Bikas said Papoulias never 
promised not to obstruct operations. Bikas was commenting on 
reports that the claim was made during the Zurich meeting 
between Papoulias and Albanian Foreign Minister Alfred Serreqi, 
and that the Greek side supposedly accepted it. 

