<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis Praises `Courageous' Israel-PLO Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kliridhis Praises `Courageous' Israel-PLO Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0505121794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 5 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0505121794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In a written statement today, President Glavkos 
Kliridhis stressed that the signing of the Israeli-PLO agreement 
has already gone down in history as a courageous and significant 
step toward peace that will have a positive effect on the Middle 
East and the rest of the world. In his statement, Kliridhis 
hails the international community's interest in the Middle East 
issue and appeals for greater support by the international 
community, particularly the Security Council, to resolve the 
Cyprus issue. 
  Kliridhis said: If the Turkish side remains a prisoner of 
the 
past, then the Cyprus issue will remain a source of disputes and 
danger that could poison the atmosphere in the entire region. 

