<H3> <TI>   Trade Unions To Hold Joint Forum </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trade Unions To Hold Joint Forum </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0505124394 Nicosia CYPRUS NEWS AGENCY in English 1712 GMT 
4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0505124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia CYPRUS NEWS AGENCY </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nicosia, May 4 (CNA)--Trade unions from both sides 
of the barbed wire which divides Cyprus since the 1974 Turkish 
invasion met Wednesday [4 May] at the free areas to discuss how 
they can play a role in building trust and understanding between 
the Greek and Turkish Cypriot communities. 
  In a joint announcement, the six trade unions (three from 
each side) said they decided to stage jointly next November a 
trade union forum in which all labour organisations of Greek and 
Turkish Cypriots will participate. 
  An effort will be made so that the forum will be held under 
the auspices of the European Union while experts from European 
trade unions will be invited to attend. The forum will address 
labour and social-economic issues of common interest. 
  Those attending today's meeting were PASIDI [Pancyprian 
Union 
of Civil Servants], PEO [Pancyprian Labor Federation], SEK 
[Confederation of Cypriot Workers], and three Turkish Cypriot 
unions namely KTAMS, DEV IS and TURK SEN. 
  The joint statement said that the six labour organisations 
"reaffirmed their determination to step up their efforts in 
order to promote and consolidate trust between the two 
communities". 
  It said the common interest and destiny of the two 
communities demanded their cooperation through mutual 
understanding for the joint handling of problems and the 
overcoming of obstacles. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

