BFN 

  [Text] Bonn, May 5 KYODO -- Japanese Prime Minister 
Tsutomu Hata arrived in Bonn from Paris on Thursday [5 May] 
afternoon on the third leg of his tour of four European 
countries. 
  Hata will meet with German Chancellor Helmut Kohl later in 
the day to discuss trade and economic relations between the two 
countries, officials said. 
  The prime minister has already visited Italy and France and 
will proceed to Belgium after Germany. 

