<H3> <TI>   NATO's Joulwan Urges Diplomatic Solution in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NATO's Joulwan Urges Diplomatic Solution in Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0805100694 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0014 GMT 8 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0805100694 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Berlin (DDP/ADN) -- General George A. Joulwan, NATO 
supreme allied commander Europe, backs a diplomatic solution for 
solving the Bosnia crisis. In any case, it is up to the United 
Nations and not NATO to decide on procedures and actions in the 
Balkans, the U.S. four-star general told BERLINER MORGENPOST. 
  Joulwan rejected the view that NATO is doing too little in 
Bosnia. After all, the alliance is monitoring the flight ban 
over Bosnia as well as deploying ships to ensure an effective 
embargo imposed on rump Yugoslavia. In addition, NATO has 
16,000 troops in Bosnia under U.N. command. 

</TEXT>

