<H3> <TI>   Turkmenistan To Join NATO Partnership for Peace </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkmenistan To Join NATO Partnership for Peace </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0605134394 Paris AFP in English 13-7 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0605134394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, May 6 (AFP) -- Turkmenistan is to join 
NATO's Partnership for Peace cooperation programme on Tuesday 
[10 May], the North Atlantic Treaty Organisation announced 
Friday. 
  Deputy Prime Minister Boris Shikhmuradov will sign the 
framework agreement at NATO's Brussels headquarters, joining 17 
other countries including Sweden and Finland, who are due to 
sign on Monday. 
  The Partnership, offered to former East Bloc countries in 
January as an alternative to enlarging the Western security 
alliance, provides for joint manoevres, military planning and 
peacekeeping operations. 

</TEXT>

