<H3> <TI>   EU `Eager' To Help New South African Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EU `Eager' To Help New South African Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0605201994 Paris AFP in English 1859 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0605201994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, May 6 (AFP) -- The European Union [EU] 
said here Friday [6 May] that it was eager to help the new 
government of South Africa to establish "a democratic and 
nonracial society." 
  Theodoros Pangalos, Greek chairman of the EU's Council of 
Ministers, said the Union was ready to embark on an economic and 
political dialogue with the new government aimed at quickly 
boosting economic trade and aid. 
  "The EU warmly welcomes the holding of the first democratic 
elections in South Africa and congratulates all the people of 
South Africa and its leaders on this historic occasion," he said 
at a meeting of development aid ministers. 
  Pangalos added the EU's confidence that all parties in South 
Africa would meet the commitments they made during negotiations 
leading up to last week's all-race elections, and would pursue 
peaceful dialogue. 

</TEXT>

