<H3> <TI>   Firm Suspected of Prohibited Trade With Libya </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Firm Suspected of Prohibited Trade With Libya </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0605134994 Amsterdam DE VOLKSKRANT in Dutch 6 May 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> BR0605134994 </F>
<F P=104>  Amsterdam DE VOLKSKRANT </F>
<F P=105>  Dutch </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Eurabic Again Suspected of Banned </F>
Trading With Libya"] 
  [Excerpt] Eurabic International, based in Hoofddorp, has 
again been caught possibly engaged in banned trading with Libya. 
The U.S. Justice Department suspects the company of supplying 
Libya with computer software. This would be an infringement of 
the U.S. [as published] trade embargo imposed on Libya. 
  Eurabic is well-known to Western intelligence services as a 
front for the Libyan Government. Netherlands Intelligence 
believes that the firm is controlled directly from Tripoli and 
attempts to acquire a variety of goods which are no longer 
available through normal channels due to the trade embargo. 
  Eurabic was founded by B. Rhuma, former head of the 
Netherlands office of Libyan Arab Airlines, the Libyan state 
airline. The U.S. Justice Department has long been interested 
in the affairs of Eurabic. In the past, Libya has purchased 
items including aircraft components and chemicals from the firm. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

