<H3> <TI>   Sinn Fein Leader To Visit Basque Area 9 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sinn Fein Leader To Visit Basque Area 9 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0605215994 London PRESS ASSOCIATION in English 2143 GMT 6 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0605215994 </F>
<F P=104>  London PRESS ASSOCIATION </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Deric Henderson, PRESS ASSOCIATION News] </F>
  [Text] Sinn Fein President Gerry Adams is to visit Spain's 
Basque region next week. 
  Mr. Adams, who arrives in Spain on Monday [9 May] for a 
three-day visit, is to have talks with Herri Batasuna (HB), the 
political arm of the separatist group ETA [Basque Fatherland and 
Liberty]. 
  One of the Basque region's MEPs [member of European 
Parliament] was in Belfast two months ago when he met Sinn Fein 
members. 
  A Sinn Fein spokesman confirmed tonight: "He is going to 
talk 
about the peace process and to explain to people there what is 
happening in Ireland. He has accepted a number of invitations." 
  Mr. Adams, who was in America earlier this year, is now 
fighting through the courts seeking to have an exclusion order 
banning him from Britain lifted. 
  Basque media and HB members said the visit was an historic 
encounter between two independent movements. 
  "Relations between the Irish and Basque people and between 
Sinn Fein and Batasuna is based on mutual solidarity for the 
fight that both peoples carry out for self-determination and 
independence." 

</TEXT>

