<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Navy Needs More Vessels for Expanded Territory </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Navy Needs More Vessels for Expanded Territory </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0805153394 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1000 GMT 8 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0805153394 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rear Admiral Sakari Visa, the commander of the Navy, 
thinks that expanding Finland's territorial waters may cause 
problems in safeguarding sufficient supervision of those waters. 
In an interview for the daily TURUN SANOMAT, Visa says that the 
Navy would first need a new patrol squadron of four to five 
vessels as well as fixed supervisory equipment so that the 
supervision of an expanded sea area could be managed properly. 
  Before the end of this month, the government intends to 
submit to the Eduskunta a proposal to move the territorial 
waters limit. The move would multiply Finland's territorial 
water area but the Navy has not been promised any additional 
equipment or staff. Visa would also like Finland to have its 
own submarines. He notes that a squadron of submarines for 
Finland would crucially facilitate supervision and would raise 
the threshold of frontier violations. According to Visa, 
nevertheless the submarines are not the top priority on the 
Navy's list of purchases. 

</TEXT>

