<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Reaffirms Position on 21 Mar UN Document </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Reaffirms Position on 21 Mar UN Document </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0805115594 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 8 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0805115594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Greek Cypriot side is expecting the UN 
Secretary General's report to record the facts objectively and 
as they stand and to put the blame where it belongs--that is, 
entirely on the Turkish side. This was said by Government 
spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis during his speech at the special 
district congress of the DISI [Democratic Rally] Youth 
Organization [NEDISI] in Larnaca. 
  Mr. Kasoulidhis added that the Greek Cypriot side has 
accepted the contents of the suggestion in the 21 March UN 
document on the condition that it also be accepted by the other 
side. He also said that our side could also make many demands 
for improvements to its own benefit, but it has not done so in 
order to facilitate reaching an agreement. Mr. Kasoulidhis 
continued: This acceptance has brought us to the end of the 
road and constitutes our maximum as far as constructive 
intentions and noble gestures. The spokesman added: As 
President Glavkos Kliridhis has also stressed clearly, our 
position is crystal clear: We will accept neither a new 
document nor changes in the current one. Mr. Kasoulidhis 
accused the Turkish side of lacking the political will to accept 
not only the confidence-building measures but also a Cyprus 
solution. 
  A message of greetings from the Greek New Democracy party 
chairman was read and North Epirotes [Greeks from southern 
Albania] also addressed the NEDISI congress, which was devoted 
to the enslaved homelands of Hellenism. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

