<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Replies to Berisha's Remarks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Replies to Berisha's Remarks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0805184194 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1500 GMT 8 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0805184194 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Replying to new remarks by Albanian President Sali 
Berisha, government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos today asked 
for respect for international law regulations regarding the 
Greek minority's human rights in Albania. 
  In an interview, Berisha again attacked our country and 
called on it to choose between the European or Byzantine trend 
which, he said, prevails in our country. 
  Venizelos said that the European trend primarily means 
respect for the principles of a state of justice, respect for 
human rights and of course respect for the rights of the Greek 
minority in Albania. Beyond that, said Venizelos, I do not 
think that many strongly worded statements help to cultivate 
good relations between the two countries. The good relations, 
he continued, definitely depend on respect for the rules I 
mentioned above. 

</TEXT>

