<H3> <TI>   Karayalcin: `We Disappove of Discussion' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karayalcin: `We Disappove of Discussion' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0605192394 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 6 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0605192394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Murat Karayalcin, state minister and deputy prime 
minister, has said: We disapprove of the intensive discussions 
on the extension of the chief of staff's term in office. 
Stating that only the government has the right to extend the 
chief of staff's term, Karayalcin added that his term will be 
extended if it is deemed necessary; if not, it will not be 
extended. 
  According to information obtained by TRT correspondent 
Mustafa Cevik, Karayalcin was answering correspondents questions 
on board a plane on his way to Sanliurfa. In answer to a 
question on whether the chief of staff's term will be extended, 
Karayalcin said: 
  [Begin Karayalcin recording] When an issue of this kind is 
discussed, it should be brief and to the point. In the letter 
the chief of the staff sent to me concerning these discussions, 
he clearly states that he has no requests regarding his term in 
office. I think that these discussions should be ended. [end 
recording] 
  In answer to another question, Karayalcin said the 
democratization package has not yet been approved. Referring to 
speculations regarding this issue, Karayalcin said: You cannot 
hold discussions on a package that is not ready. How can I or 
Prime Minister Ciller discuss the democratization package with 
other people if it is not ready yet? 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

