<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gures Comments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gures Comments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0605160794 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1555 GMT 6 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0605160794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, May 6 (A.A.) -- Chief of Staff General 
Dogan Gures told the Anatolian Agency on Friday [6 May] that the 
polemics on the extension of duty for the chief of staff should 
be searched for outside his office. 
  Gures said he has explained his opinion on the issue on many 
occasions, adding that when the time comes to transfer duty, 
`those who conduct this duty with honor, hand it over to the 
next commander with pride. I have already said this is how it 
will happen, weeks ago at a meeting where the highest government 
officials were present.' 
  He said there is always available personnel for every post 
in 
the Turkish Armed Forces. 
  `In the armed forces, no one can expect any favor and one 
does not accept any,' Gures said adding that one refrains as 
much as possible from showing negative intentions. 
  He also thanked Prime Minister Tansu Ciller who made a 
statement on the issue. 
  Earlier on Friday, Ciller said that the authority to extend 
the term of duty of the chief of staff belongs entirely to the 
political authority. 
  A statement published by the Office of the Prime Ministry 
said that `we may see it profitable and necessary for the 
country's well being, to preserve the present command team on 
duty under its present shape.' 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

