<H3> <TI>   Three Explosions Reported in Istanbul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Three Explosions Reported in Istanbul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0705151594 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1200 
GMT 7 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0705151594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] There were three different explosions in Istanbul 
today. One person was injured. According to information 
received by a TRT correspondent from security officials, a bomb 
placed by unidentified persons in the public toilet in the 
Sultanahmet Square exploded around 1030. The explosion started 
a fire in the toilet. Ibrahim Kazman was injured in the 
incident. He was taken to Hasiki Hospital and he is reported to 
be in satisfactory condition. 
  Around the same time, another bomb exploded under a bench 
opposite the rector's office of Marmara University in 
Sultanahmet Square. The bomb caused material damage. 
  The third bomb was placed in the bus parking lot near the 
Dolmabahce Palace. The explosion, which occurred around 1100, 
wrecked a motorcycle in the parking lot, but no one was killed 
or injured. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

