<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over still of Golhan] </F>
  [Text] Defense Minister Mehmet Golhan, who is on an 
official visit to France, has begun his contacts. He met with 
French Defense Minister Francois Leotard in Paris today. 
International issues such as Bosnia-Herzegovina and Azerbaijan, 
Turkey's relations with the European Union, and bilateral ties 
were discussed at the meeting. Golhan also briefed Leotard on 
terrorist activities in Turkey and the struggle being waged 
against terrorism. Leotard said that France will continue to 
support Turkey's struggle against terrorism. Golhan will visit 
Toulon and Marseilles today. 

</TEXT>

