BFN 

  [Text] After Alain Juppe's remarks this morning, Francois 
Leotard has said he thinks that nuclear tests should continue. 
The defense minister restated this before the finance committee 
of the National Assembly. He is thus in complete disagreement 
with Francois Mitterrand who yesterday afternoon reaffirmed his 
determination to maintain the moratorium on French nuclear 
testing. 

</TEXT>

