<H4>    Germany Flies 214 to Djibouti </H4>

<F P=102> AU0805171994 Hamburg DPA in German 1342 GMT 8 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0805171994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- A second group of German citizens was 
evacuated from the Yemeni capital of Sanaa on Sunday [8 May] 
with the help of the Bundeswehr. According to the Defense 
Ministry in Bonn, an aircraft with 107 passengers on board 
landed in Djibouti, East Africa, in the afternoon, another 
aircraft also carrying 107 passengers is on its way. 
  A third flight that was originally announced for Sunday will 
presumably not take place before Monday. According to a Foreign 
Ministry spokesperson, 280 Germans who want to leave Yemen 
appeared at the German Embassy in Sanaa throughout the day. 
  Another special Lufthansa plane is expected in Frankfurt 
from 
Djibouti on Monday afternoon. It will have approximately 200 
passengers on board. 

</TEXT>

