<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Djibouti-Sanaa Air Corridor Opened"] </F>
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, May 9 -- An Italian Air Force C-130 
transport plane last night flew some 100 refugees of various 
nationalities from Sanaa, North Yemen, to Djibouti while a 
second C-130 is currently on a similar mission, Italian military 
sources said. 
  In contrast to initial reports, the first plane load of 
refugees were not Italian but composed of 33 French nationals, 
30 Djibouti natives, four Algerians, one Iranian, one American, 
five Syrians, seven Somalis, two Egyptians, two Canadians, four 
Moroccans, three Tunisians and eight children of various 
nationalities. 
  The second C-130, military sources added, should bring to 
Djibouti between 50 to 55 Italian nationals, who will be 
immediately taken to Italy. 

</TEXT>

