<F P=106> [Article signed BB: "Talks on East Timor Have Resumed in </F>
Geneva"] 
  [Text] Geneva, 6 May (ATS) -- The fourth series of talks 
between Portugal and Indonesia on the future of East Timor 
started in Geneva this morning under UN auspices. UN Secretary 
General Butrus Butrus-Ghali is meeting Ali Alatas and Durao 
Barroso, the Indonesian and Portuguese foreign ministers, 
respectively. At meetings in New York last September, both 
countries pledged to take measures to ease the situation in that 
former Portuguese colony, which was annexed by Indonesia in 1975 
right after it became independent. The occupation of East Timor 
has never been recognized by the international community. 
Several organizations have blamed Indonesia for human rights 
abuses there. 

</TEXT>

