<H3> <TI>   Commission Tests Nuclear Emergency Plans </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Commission Tests Nuclear Emergency Plans </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0605131994 London REUTER Textline Database in English 5 
May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0605131994 </F>
<F P=104>  London REUTER Textline Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article from Brussels EUROPE: "EU Commission </F>
Organises Emergency Response Exercise in Case of a Nuclear 
Catastrophe"] 
  [Text] The European Commission, the German Laender of 
Rheinland-Palatine and Baden-Wurttemberg, as well as the nuclear 
power plant of Karlsruhe (Germany) are organising from Thursday 
[5 May], near the nuclear power plant of Phillipsburg, an 
emergency response exercise, called EUROPA 94, to last until 
Saturday 7 May inclusive. The object of the exercise, in which 
representatives from EU [European Union] Member States, 
international organisations and experts from some Central and 
East European countries will take part, is to test the 
implementation of different emergency plans provided for in case 
of a nuclear catastrophe; it is also intended to encourage an 
exchange of views and experiences between those responsible for 
emergency services in the different countries, so as to 
guarantee a maximum amount of cooperation and communication in 
case of a real catastrophe. The European Commissioner 
responsible for European policy in matters of civil protection, 
Ioannis Paleokrassis, stressed the importance of such an 
exercise. 

</TEXT>

